 The 91-year-old actress looked barely a few years older than her I Dream of Jeannie days in the 1960s. Barbara Eden attended the star-studded Remus Pre Award Tea Time event at The Beverly Hills Hotel on Wednesday. The celebrated singer appeared in a blue jacket, comfortable black trousers and statement sparkling earrings. The actress sported her iconic blonde fringe and curly locks loose as she smiled with her celebrity pals, Kate Linder and Morgan Fairchild. Barbara starred in the iconic American sitcom I Dream of Jeannie, playing a genie named Jeannie.